e and other cases, offering practical suggestions for diverse participants in community-based initiatives and their supporters, agencies and interest groups, and researchers and educators.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aCommunity organizationzWest (U.S.)vCase studies. 0aNatural resourcesxGovernment policyzWest (U.S.)vCase studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / General.2bisacsh1 aBrunner, Ronald D., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aColburn, Christine H., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aColburn, Christine H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCromley, Christina M., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aCromley, Christina M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlein, Roberta A., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aKlein, Roberta A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOlson, Elizabeth A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030012790440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300127904423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300127904/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles